cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper examines the interplay between social networks and topical affiliations on Twitter, which involves analyzing graph structures and set structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering), which both deal with network analysis. The paper also touches on topics related to social networks, such as predicting social relationships and hashtag popularity, which could place it in the cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing hashtag usage, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
